00:40:25,640 --> 00:40:32,440
It's marvelous how different Dante's view of evil is from the Protestant view of evil.

358
00:40:32,600 --> 00:40:42,440
For Dante, they are immobile, frozen in ice, and that's because you need just one phrase to understand it.

359
00:40:43,080 --> 00:40:52,201
If you're open to the attractiveness of things, then you are moved by the light, food, or romantic love again, and so forth.

360
00:40:52,201 --> 00:40:55,241
And now it's a pun on move, the way I'm saying it.

361
00:40:55,241 --> 00:40:58,921
When you're moved by something, you are literally moved.

362
00:40:58,921 --> 00:41:01,960
That is, you don't do anything or act.

363
00:41:02,281 --> 00:41:13,400
