364
00:41:13,721 --> 00:41:26,480
And that means if you reject God's creation and its attractiveness and want to be autonomous, then you get less and less moved the more autonomous you get.

365
00:41:27,361 --> 00:41:33,121
So if you got to be completely autonomous, you'd be completely immobilized.

366
00:41:33,120 --> 00:41:35,841
Nothing would be attractive for you.

367
00:41:36,160 --> 00:41:56,881
And since nothing was attractive for you, since all attractiveness finally comes from God, and you rejected God, then you are just, and you are cold because you aren't emotionally involved, you aren't passionate, you aren't loving, you aren't open to anything.

368
00:41:56,881 --> 00:42:01,680
I mean, even the guy who loves his white BMW convertible isn't cold.

369
00:42:02,160 --> 00:42:10,641
He's got a rather limited object, and he's over, he's obviously over-committed to it.

370
00:42:10,640 --> 00:42:19,521
But to be really, really cold is to have no attractions at all because you're so self-sufficient.

371
00:42:19,520 --> 00:42:28,641
And that is so prideful that you won't accept to give up your willpower for the attractiveness of anything.

372
00:42:28,960 --> 00:42:33,121
That's then, you know, the line better to rule in hell than serve in heaven.

373
00:42:33,120 --> 00:42:41,201
And if you won't give up your willpower for anything, finally you won't be moved by anything.

374
00:42:41,201 --> 00:42:43,281
And that's why you're in the ice.

375
00:42:44,241 --> 00:42:57,440
And that's that, the ice is just the realization of that, that is the sort of dramatization of the fact that these people are cold and not moved by anything.

376
00:42:57,440 --> 00:43:17,161
The more you get to the bottom, the more you find people who have turned against their lords, their bosses, their brothers, their family, their country, and the more we find these sinners who, having refused all attractions, are just like rocks.

377
00:43:17,160 --> 00:43:22,361
Dante kicks one of the heads of the people frozen in ice, and Virgil says that's a good thing.

